00240 /*
00241  * Get the probe set type.
00242  */
00243 affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType FusionCDFQCProbeSetInformation::GetQCProbeSetType() const
00244 {
00245         if (gcosSet)
00246                 return gcosSet->GetQCProbeSetType();
00247         else if (calvinSet)
00248         {
00249                 affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType qcType=affxcdf::UnknownQCProbeSetType;
00250                 const std::wstring &qc = calvinSet->GetQCProbeSetType();
00251                 for (int i=(int)affxcdf::UnknownQCProbeSetType; i<=(int)affxcdf::SpatialNormalizationPositiveQCProbeSetType; i++)
00252                 {
00253                         if (qc == FusionCDFQCProbeSetNames::GetStaticCDFQCProbeSetName((affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType)i))
00254                         {
00255                                 qcType = (affxcdf::GeneChipQCProbeSetType)i;
00256                                 break;
00257                         }
00258                 }
00259                 return qcType;
00260         }
00261         else
00262                 return affxcdf::UnknownQCProbeSetType;
00263 }

00517 /*
00518  * Get the groups direction.
00519  */
00520 affxcdf::DirectionType FusionCDFProbeGroupInformation::GetDirection() const
00521 {
00522         if (gcosGroup)
00523                 return gcosGroup->GetDirection();
00524         else if (calvinGroup)
00525         {
00526                 DirectionType dir = calvinGroup->GetDirection();
00527                 switch (dir)
00528                 {
00529                 case ProbeNoDirection:
00530                         return affxcdf::NoDirection;
00531                         break;
00532 
00533                 case ProbeSenseDirection:
00534                         return affxcdf::SenseDirection;
00535                         break;
00536 
00537                 case ProbeAntiSenseDirection:
00538                         return affxcdf::AntiSenseDirection;
00539                         break;
00540 
00541                 case ProbeEitherDirection:
00542                         return affxcdf::EitherDirection;
00543                         break;
00544 
00545                 default:
00546                         return affxcdf::NoDirection;
00547                         break;
00548                 }
00549         }
00550         else
00551                 return affxcdf::NoDirection;
00552 }

00679 /*
00680  * Get the probe replication type.
00681  */
00682 affxcdf::ReplicationType FusionCDFProbeGroupInformation::GetRepType() const
00683 {
00684         if (gcosGroup)
00685                 return gcosGroup->GetRepType();
00686         else if (calvinGroup)
00687         {
00688                 ReplicationType rep = calvinGroup->GetRepType();
00689                 switch (rep)
00690                 {
00691                 case UnknownProbeRepType:
00692                         return affxcdf::UnknownRepType;
00693                         break;
00694 
00695                 case DifferentProbeRepType:
00696                         return affxcdf::DifferentRepType;
00697                         break;
00698 
00699                 case MixedProbeRepType:
00700                         return affxcdf::MixedRepType;
00701                         break;
00702 
00703                 case IdenticalProbeRepType:
00704                         return affxcdf::IdenticalRepType;
00705                         break;
00706 
00707                 default:
00708                         return affxcdf::UnknownRepType;
00709                         break;
00710                 }
00711         }
00712         else
00713                 return affxcdf::UnknownRepType;
00714 }

01091 /*
01092  * Get the chip type (probe array type) of the CDF file.
01093  * This is the name of the file without extension.
01094  */
01095 std::string FusionCDFData::GetChipType() const
01096 {
01097         int index = (int) fileName.rfind('\\');
01098         if (index == -1)
01099                 index = (int) fileName.rfind('/');
01100         std::string chiptype = fileName.c_str() + index + 1;
01101         chiptype.resize(chiptype.length()-4);
01102         return chiptype;
01103 }
01104 
01105 /*
01106  * Get the chip type (probe array type) of the CDF file.
01107  * This is the name of the file without extension. We
01108  * also include all substrings create by removing
01109  * characters to the right of each '.'
01110  */
01111 std::vector<std::string> FusionCDFData::GetChipTypes() const
01112 {
01113     std::vector<std::string> chiptypes;
01114     std::string chiptype;
01115 
01116         int index = (int) fileName.rfind('\\');
01117         if (index == -1)
01118                 index = (int) fileName.rfind('/');
01119         chiptype = fileName.c_str() + index + 1;
01120         chiptype.resize(chiptype.length()-4);
01121 
01122     // The full file name (minus .cdf extension) is the default (1st) 
01123     // chip type. This matches what GetChipType() returns.
01124     // ie: foo.bar.v1.r2.cdf -> foo.bar.v1.r2
01125     chiptypes.push_back(chiptype);
01126 
01127     //We then add all substrings starting at zero and ending at '.'
01128     // ie: foo.bar.v1.r2.cdf -> foo.bar.v1, foo.bar, foo
01129     std::string::size_type pos = chiptype.rfind(".",chiptype.size()-1);
01130     while (pos != std::string::npos){
01131         if(pos>0)
01132             chiptypes.push_back(chiptype.substr(0,pos));
01133         pos = chiptype.rfind(".",pos-1);
01134     }
01135 
01136     //ie: foo.bar.v1.r2, foo.bar.v1, foo.bar, foo
01137         return chiptypes;
01138 }

01229 /*
01230  * Determines if a CDF file is of the Calvin format.
01231  */
01232 bool FusionCDFData::IsCalvinCompatibleFile(const char *fileName)
01233 {
01234         GenericData data;
01235         GenericFileReader reader;
01236         reader.SetFilename(fileName);
01237         try
01238         {
01239                 reader.ReadHeader(data, GenericFileReader::ReadNoDataGroupHeader);
01240                 return true;
01241         }
01242         catch (affymetrix_calvin_exceptions::CalvinException)
01243         {
01244         }
01245         return false;
01246 }

01248 /*
01249  * Get the probe set type for non-qc probe sets.
01250  */
01251 affxcdf::GeneChipProbeSetType FusionCDFData::GetProbeSetType(int index) const
01252 {
01253         if (gcosData)
01254         {
01255                 return gcosData->GetProbeSetType(index);
01256         }
01257         else if (calvinData && calvinData->GetGenericData().Header().GetGenericDataHdr()->GetFileTypeId() != AFFY_CNTRL_PS)
01258         {
01259                 std::string dataTypeId = calvinData->GetDataTypeId();
01260                 if (dataTypeId == AFFY_EXPR_PS)
01261                         return affxcdf::ExpressionProbeSetType;
01262 
01263                 else if (dataTypeId == AFFY_GENO_PS)
01264                         return affxcdf::GenotypingProbeSetType;
01265 
01266                 else if (dataTypeId == AFFY_RESEQ_PS)
01267                         return affxcdf::ResequencingProbeSetType;
01268 
01269                 else if (dataTypeId == AFFY_TAG_PS)
01270                         return affxcdf::TagProbeSetType;
01271 
01272                 else
01273                         return affxcdf::UnknownProbeSetType;
01274         }
01275         else
01276                 return affxcdf::UnknownProbeSetType;
01277 }
